		"notes": [
			{
				"category": "summary",
				"text": "New Red Hat Single Sign-On 7.4.6 packages are now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8.\n\nRed Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Low. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.",
				"title": "Topic"
			},
			{
				"category": "general",
				"text": "Red Hat Single Sign-On is a standalone server, based on the Keycloak project, that provides authentication and standards-based single sign-on capabilities for web and mobile applications.\n\nThis release of Red Hat Single Sign-On 7.4.6 on RHEL 8 serves as a replacement for Red Hat Single Sign-On 7.4.5, and includes bug fixes and enhancements, which are documented in the Release Notes document linked to in the References.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* nodejs-angular: XSS due to regex-based HTML replacement (CVE-2020-7676)\n\n* keycloak: reusable \"state\" parameter at redirect_uri endpoint enables possibility of replay attacks (CVE-2020-14302)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
				"title": "Details"
			},
			{
				"category": "legal_disclaimer",
